		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's a bit lame of me to ask you guys to help me on a project that has nothing to do with NESDev, especially after being so inactive here as of late, but it's for a graded school project, so... <img src="./images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /><br /><br />Anyway, I had to do a stop motion project with my theatre class, and upon initially taking pictures, I forgot to take my camera's lighting off auto, so you have some pictures that are super saturated and yellow tinted, (luckily, all the bad lighting looks exactly the same) which is bad in of itself, but is even worse because I can't get it to work with Chroma Key in Sony Vegas which means the green screen randomly reappears in some shots.<br /><br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<a href="./download/file.php?id=12451&amp;mode=view"><img src="./download/file.php?id=12451&amp;t=1" alt="Bad Picture.png" /></a><br />
